com.ibm.team.scm.common

Interface IVersionedContent


  • public interface IVersionedContent
    Represents a description of content that is stored in the repository. The actual contents (e.g. the bytes) are stored and retrieved using an IVersionedContentManager or its component specific subclass, and this description is the identity of the bytes.
    Since:
    0.7

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ContentHash getHash()
      Returns the hash for the content as stored on the server.
      IVersionableHandle getOriginalContainingState()
      Returns the state handle that this content is stored in on the server.
      long getSize()
      Returns the uncompressed size for the content as stored on the server.
      boolean sameContent(IVersionedContent other)
      Returns whether the receiver represents semantically the same content as the one passed in.

    • Method Detail

      • getHash

        ContentHash getHash()
        Returns the hash for the content as stored on the server. Note: this is not a unique identifier for the content, as subclasses may add semantic meaning such that although the bytes as stored on the server are identical (and thus the hashes are identical) the semantic interpretation is different.

      • getSize

        long getSize()
        Returns the uncompressed size for the content as stored on the server.

      • getOriginalContainingState

        IVersionableHandle getOriginalContainingState()
        Returns the state handle that this content is stored in on the server. If this content has only been uploaded and not stored in any item then this method returns null.

      • sameContent

        boolean sameContent(IVersionedContent other)
        Returns whether the receiver represents semantically the same content as the one passed in.
